<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-18T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-18T22:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-18T21:00:00-06:00">April 18, 1931—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>59. My 58, April 18, 2 p.m. Following just received from American Vice
                            Consul at Ceiba: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Send warship immediately, American lives in
                            danger.”</p></quote></p>
                        <p>I approve and urge immediate action. Details follow by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>